# Kotlin Style

## Null Safety – Direct Safe Calls

Prefer **direct safe calls** over redundant `let` when only invoking a single method:

```kotlin
// Preferred
currentGameLoopPhase?.onStop(context)

// Avoid – redundant let
currentGameLoopPhase?.let { phase -> phase.onStop(context) }
```

Use `?.let { }` only when you need the non-null value for multiple operations or to assign to a variable.

## Property Declaration

Prefer **direct assignment** over getter syntax when declaring properties:

```kotlin
// Preferred
override val arenaId: ArenaId = arena.id

// Avoid
override val arenaId: ArenaId
    get() = arena.id
```

Use `get() = ...` only when the value **changes at runtime** and must be recomputed on each access (e.g. delegating to mutable state).

## Parameters – Direct Values, No Lambdas

Pass values directly instead of wrapping them in lambdas when the value is known at call site:

```kotlin
// Preferred
class StatsServiceImpl(
    private val plugin: JavaPlugin,
    private val loadedGames: List<MicroGame>,
)

StatsServiceImpl(plugin, gameLoader.loadedGames)

// Avoid – unnecessary lambda
class StatsServiceImpl(
    private val plugin: JavaPlugin,
    private val loadedGames: () -> List<MicroGame>,
)

StatsServiceImpl(plugin) { gameLoader.loadedGames }
```

Use lambdas only when you need lazy evaluation or the value changes over time.

## Method Bodies – Logical Spacing

Add blank lines between logical blocks inside methods. Do not cram all statements together:

```kotlin
// Preferred
override fun record(scope: StatScope.Player, key: StatKey, value: Number) {
    val definition = getDefinition(key) ?: return
    val file = getPlayerGameFile(scope.playerId, key.gameId)
    val current = loadStats(file)

    val currentVal = current[key.statId.value]?.toDouble() ?: definition.defaultValue.toDouble()
    val newVal = when (definition.aggregation) { ... }

    current[key.statId.value] = newVal
    saveStats(file, current)
}

// Avoid – everything cramped
override fun record(scope: StatScope.Player, key: StatKey, value: Number) {
    val definition = getDefinition(key) ?: return
    val file = getPlayerGameFile(scope.playerId, key.gameId)
    val current = loadStats(file)
    val currentVal = current[key.statId.value]?.toDouble() ?: definition.defaultValue.toDouble()
    val newVal = when (definition.aggregation) { ... }
    current[key.statId.value] = newVal
    saveStats(file, current)
}
```
